# Git and Commit Rules

## Author identity (must be correct on GitHub)

Commits in this repository must be authored as:

- `user.name`: `trhlow`
- `user.email`: `thlong190705@gmail.com`

Before committing, verify:

```powershell
git config user.name
git config user.email
```

If a repo-local override exists, it wins over global config. Prefer keeping repo-local identity correct OR remove local overrides so global identity applies.

## Commit style

Use Conventional Commits where possible:

- `feat: ...`
- `fix: ...`
- `refactor: ...`
- `test: ...`
- `docs: ...`
- `chore: ...`

## Commit granularity

- One logical change per commit (avoid mixing unrelated refactors + features + formatting sweeps).

## Before pushing

- Ensure working tree is intentional
- Prefer `git status` / `git diff` review for risky changes

## History rewriting

Avoid rewriting published history unless necessary. If you must rewrite `main`, coordinate because it requires force-push.
